        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2014-08-02 06:54:46.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n(1 comment)\n\nI don't really get the \"Any site could be matched\" wording in the description.\nI read the jira ticket and it was not any more clear.\n\nthe FAULT_ANY flag kind of makes sense, but it's not implemented here.\n\nOtherwise any regular CFS_FAIL site could be matched too - you just write the fail_lock with the correct id.\n\nSo is the intention here to be able to trigger any operation with interlapping bits in the fail_loc (e.g. due to the same subsystem, though values there do interlap too as I see) with a single value no matter what operation happens to be unlucky one to fail?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "79c55ff07ddabbbebd44f268ae114ac8e35bdc88",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 177,
        "name": "John Hammond",
        "email": "jhammond@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jhammond"
      },
      "date": "2014-08-02 16:32:10.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n(1 comment)\n\n> I don't really get the \"Any site could be matched\" wording in the description. I read the jira ticket and it was not any more clear.\n\nReturn -EFAULT 1% of the time a CFS_FAULT_CHECK() instrumented operation is called:\n\n \nlctl set_param fail_loc=0x0A000000\nlctl set_param fail_val=100\nlctl set_param fail_err=-14\n\nMake dt_declare_create() fail with -EFAULT 1% of the time:\n\n \nlctl set_param fail_loc=0x0800200b\nlctl set_param fail_val=100\nlctl set_param fail_err=-14\n\n> the FAULT_ANY flag kind of makes sense, but it's not implemented here.\n\nThat's called CFS_FAULT now. I have updated the Jira ticket.\n\n> Otherwise any regular CFS_FAIL site could be matched too - you just write the fail_lock with the correct id.\n\n> So is the intention here to be able to trigger any operation with interlapping bits in the fail_loc (e.g. due to the same subsystem, though values there do interlap too as I see) with a single value no matter what operation happens to be unlucky one to fail?\n\nNo. Seem my comment inline.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
